column10:
I've played Anno 1404 since it came out on disc. Now, I've found it again and upgraded to the History Edition. The attention to detail (especially in the graphics and animations) still astounds me today. I've always found it a seamless and immersive experience, and really love the personalities of the AI players. For some reason, I'm really attracted to the Corsair King. XD  

It's been really brilliant playing this again, at a custom level too, for being able to change many modifiers to make your next game exactly as you want it. This is the best instalment of the Anno Series because of the versatility of play, the three different factions, the two huge cities you have to build and warehouse micro-management. 

A big thumbs up from me. :}
